      "properties": {
        "text": ""
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "\u2139\ufe0f Lens Distortion Corrector (S-07)\n\nDefaults: preset=canon_24mm_wide, direction=inverse.\n\n- preset: 4 calibrated approximations + 'custom' + 'no_op_identity' (safe pass-through). When preset \u2260 'custom', the 5 widget values below are overridden by the preset tuple.\n- direction:\n    inverse = rectify a distorted source (default; the retouch use case).\n    forward = simulate distortion on a clean source (creative effect, e.g. fake fisheye).\n- k1, k2, k3 (radial) and p1, p2 (tangential) follow Brown\u2013Conrady convention shared by Kornia and OpenCV. Used only when preset = 'custom'.\n\nProduction use case: drop in BEFORE face-detect / aligner. A wide-angle portrait shot at 24mm has barrel distortion that throws off landmark detection; rectifying first gives cleaner landmarks and a more natural unwarp.\n\nWarning: presets are mid-range averages, not lens-specific calibration. Pro retouch should calibrate via a checkerboard tool (OpenCV calibrateCamera) and paste the resulting (k1..p2) tuple into 'custom' for accuracy."
      ],
